{"hash":"fc7e771a82a0cbf77cb43545228142d326748723","data":{"post":{"title":"What is the difference between data, computed and methods in Vue JS","date":"July 20, 2021","content":"<p>Consider this very simple component. It gets a name and displays it inside an div. Nothing fancy here.</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki\" style=\"background-color: #2e3440ff\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;template&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">  </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;div&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">    Hello </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">{</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">{</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">name</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">}</span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">}</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">!</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">  </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/div&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/template&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;script&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">export default </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">{</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">  </span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">name</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">: </span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&#39;</span><span style=\"color: #A3BE8C\">Hello</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&#39;</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">  </span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9\">props</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">: </span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">{</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">    </span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">name</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">:</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">{</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">      </span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">type</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">:</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #8FBCBB\">String</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">      </span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">required</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">:</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">false</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">      </span><span style=\"color: #88C0D0\">default</span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">:</span><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\"> </span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">&quot;&quot;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">    </span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">}</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #D8DEE9FF\">  </span><span style=\"color: #ECEFF4\">}</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">}</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color: #81A1C1\">&lt;/script&gt;</span></span></code></pre>\n<p>But let's say I want to uppercase the name. Vue JS provides us three different options on how to do this:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://vuejs.org/v2/api/#Options-Data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">data</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://vuejs.org/v2/api/#computed\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">computed</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://vuejs.org/v2/api/#methods\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">methods</a></li>\n</ul>\n","tags":[{"title":"JavaScript","path":"/tag/JavaScript/"},{"title":"Vue JS","path":"/tag/Vue%20JS/"}]}},"context":{}}